# Multi-Cloud Patterns — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Designing or deploying Azure or GCP infrastructure
- Managing cloud resources, networking, or security groups
- Working with cloud-native services (Azure Functions, Cloud Run, etc.)

## Azure Patterns
- **Resource Groups** — Organize resources by environment/team
- **ARM/Bicep Templates** — Infrastructure as Code
- **Azure DevOps** — CI/CD pipelines
- **Key Vault** — Secret management
- **App Service / AKS** — Application hosting

## GCP Patterns
- **Projects** — Resource isolation boundaries
- **Deployment Manager / Terraform** — IaC
- **Cloud Build** — CI/CD
- **Secret Manager** — Credential storage
- **Cloud Run / GKE** — Container orchestration

## Best Practices
- Use service accounts with minimal permissions
- Enable audit logging on all cloud operations
- Tag resources with environment, team, and cost-center labels
- Store cloud credentials in environment variables, never in code
